  "corner_label": "Screen English",
  "title": "",
  "movie": "스톰 보이 (Storm Boy)",
  "duration_sec": 772.62,
  "audio_url": "https://rtyzdyyfahddqshgyjvn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/gmp-audio/2023-03-15_screen_english.mp3",
  "artwork_generated_url": "",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 3.54,
      "text": "우리 크리스 씨 오셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 3.54,
      "end": 5.26,
      "text": "Great to be here. Good morning."
    },
    {
      "start": 5.52,
      "end": 6.44,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.58,
      "end": 9.22,
      "text": "6187님께서"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.22,
      "end": 11.54,
      "text": "크쌤 반갑습니다. 정현쌤"
    },
    {
      "start": 11.54,
      "end": 13.34,
      "text": "굿모닝. 좋은 아침입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.78,
      "end": 17.22,
      "text": "Ah, you said Korean to me and English to 조쌤."
    },
    {
      "start": 17.3,
      "end": 17.94,
      "text": "그러게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 18.04,
      "end": 18.66,
      "text": "I like it."
    },
    {
      "start": 18.8,
      "end": 23.86,
      "text": "Wow. 역시 센스 있으신 6187님이셨고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 23.98,
      "end": 24.42,
      "text": "좋은 아침."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.72,
      "end": 30.74,
      "text": "네. 이 영화가 정말 아름다운 호주의 자연을 많이 보여주잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.74,
      "end": 33.32,
      "text": "근데, have you been to Australia?"
    },
    {
      "start": 33.76,
      "end": 35.24,
      "text": "I really want to go."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.38,
      "end": 36.16,
      "text": "Oh, 진짜요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 36.2,
      "end": 36.78,
      "text": "Why did you go?"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.04,
      "end": 38.8,
      "text": "아, 뭐 떠올랐어요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.8,
      "end": 43.44,
      "text": "왠지, your relatives가 살고 계시니까"
    },
    {
      "start": 43.44,
      "end": 47.64,
      "text": "Yes. My wife's sister and her husband and whole family live in Australia."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.8,
      "end": 49.84,
      "text": "Yeah, but you've never been to Australia."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.94,
      "end": 53.2,
      "text": "My wife's family has been, I have never been."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.2,
      "end": 56.78,
      "text": "When I first met my wife, she had an Australian accent"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.78,
      "end": 59.5,
      "text": "because she had just returned from Australia."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.64,
      "end": 59.88,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 60.22,
      "end": 62.76,
      "text": "So, I've been wanting to go for the past 10 years."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.42,
      "end": 64.42,
      "text": "10 whole years."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.46,
      "end": 64.68,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.92,
      "end": 66.1,
      "text": "Still have not made it."
    },
    {
      "start": 66.1,
      "end": 69.7,
      "text": "열심히 일을 하시느라 너무 바쁘셔가지고 못 가보셨나봐요."
    },
    {
      "start": 69.86,
      "end": 74.6,
      "text": "네. 집에서 잡혀있어가지고 빨리 갈 날이 왔으면 좋겠네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.78,
      "end": 78.06,
      "text": "만약에 나중에 호주에 가신다면, what would you like to do?"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.06,
      "end": 82.92,
      "text": "I would love to dine, wine and dine. I love eating, cooking and eating."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.08,
      "end": 83.44,
      "text": "그래요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.56,
      "end": 86.18,
      "text": "So, I want to try some Australian delights."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.32,
      "end": 93.3,
      "text": "The only thing that my brother-in-law, 마서방, my wife's sister's husband,"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.5,
      "end": 97.24,
      "text": "he brings me that black spread."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.48,
      "end": 99.34,
      "text": "You know the famous black spread?"
    },
    {
      "start": 99.84,
      "end": 102.18,
      "text": "호주식, 그 정말 맛없기로 유명한."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.26,
      "end": 102.5,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.62,
      "end": 103.6,
      "text": "호불호 가리기로 유명한."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.62,
      "end": 106.24,
      "text": "월터 씨도 한번 이야기해준 적이 있었던 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.24,
      "end": 111.48,
      "text": "Anyway, he sends that to us, and I still haven't figured out how to use it properly."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.82,
      "end": 116.2,
      "text": "Because if you just spread it on bread, it doesn't taste the best to me."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.44,
      "end": 118.58,
      "text": "But maybe it's an acquired taste."
    },
    {
      "start": 119.04,
      "end": 122.08,
      "text": "Anyway, I want to try some delicious 별미들 먹고 싶어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.14,
      "end": 125.22,
      "text": "그 마서방님께서는 그게 되게 별미이기 때문에,"
    },
    {
      "start": 125.6,
      "end": 128.44,
      "text": "그리고 맛있다고 생각해서 보내주셨을 텐데."
    },
    {
      "start": 128.78,
      "end": 130.64,
      "text": "아니면 그냥 크서방, 한방."
    },
    {
      "start": 130.86,
      "end": 131.38,
      "text": "당해봐라?"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.54,
      "end": 132.56,
      "text": "네, 먹이는 거지."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.72,
      "end": 133.08,
      "text": "에이."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.2,
      "end": 134.5,
      "text": "에이, 오지, 오지 마라."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.5,
      "end": 136.38,
      "text": "혹시 그 틸리 아닌 거 아니에요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.34,
      "end": 138.08,
      "text": "아, 틸리?"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.8,
      "end": 141.42,
      "text": "그 작가 이름에 대해서 마서방이 알려주셨잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 141.66,
      "end": 143.56,
      "text": "아, ignorant American."
    },
    {
      "start": 144.02,
      "end": 147.56,
      "text": "How dare you mispronounce our famous writer's name."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.3,
      "end": 150.18,
      "text": "하지만 그것은 사실인 거고,"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.56,
      "end": 154.62,
      "text": "어쨌든 호주에 아직 못 가보셨다는 소식에 되게 놀라웠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 154.62,
      "end": 156.16,
      "text": "They live in Sydney right now."
    },
    {
      "start": 156.24,
      "end": 157.88,
      "text": "They've moved all over Australia."
    },
    {
      "start": 158.2,
      "end": 161.88,
      "text": "From the countryside to the city, back to the countryside, and now they're in Sydney."
    },
    {
      "start": 162.14,
      "end": 165.5,
      "text": "The opera house, many, many delicious restaurants."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.76,
      "end": 169.1,
      "text": "I would love to visit and see my nephews and nieces."
    },
    {
      "start": 169.56,
      "end": 170.9,
      "text": "And cook and eat."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.4,
      "end": 172.7,
      "text": "Have you ever been to Australia?"
    },
    {
      "start": 172.88,
      "end": 173.96,
      "text": "아유, 그럴 리가 있겠어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.52,
      "end": 175.74,
      "text": "아유, 그럴 리가 없나봐요."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.74,
      "end": 185.36,
      "text": "아무튼 가족, 친척들을 만나기 위해서 가장 첫 번째로 오스트레일리아를 가보고 싶다라고 하실 줄 알았거든요."
    },
    {
      "start": 186.52,
      "end": 192.22,
      "text": "그런데 다인 앤 와인이 가장 먼저 나오고 2순위로 밀려난 거 캐치했습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.62,
      "end": 196.7,
      "text": "마스방이랑 크스방 그렇게 싹 지나지 못해가지고 약간 경쟁사예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 196.7,
      "end": 200.58,
      "text": "약간 거리가 있어야지 그게 가족으로서 괜찮아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 200.72,
      "end": 201.24,
      "text": "아, 그럼요."
    },
    {
      "start": 201.28,
      "end": 201.62,
      "text": "그럼요."
    },
    {
      "start": 201.64,
      "end": 202.76,
      "text": "거리 두기 어느 정도."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.66,
      "end": 206.18,
      "text": "자, 이제 영화 이야기를 또 이어가야 되는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 206.18,
      "end": 211.74,
      "text": "영화 촬영지가 호주에서도 특히 남부의 웨드랜즈하고"
    },
    {
      "start": 211.74,
      "end": 215.06,
      "text": "샌드운스 디스트릭트였잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 215.3,
      "end": 216.54,
      "text": "Yes, 샌드운스."
    },
    {
      "start": 216.94,
      "end": 223.36,
      "text": "I think of like sand buggies, really fast cars driving in sandy hills"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.36,
      "end": 225.58,
      "text": "when I hear the 샌드운스."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.58,
      "end": 225.88,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.38,
      "end": 228.28,
      "text": "But this is a very famous area."
    },
    {
      "start": 228.44,
      "end": 228.82,
      "text": "Uh-huh."
    },
    {
      "start": 228.96,
      "end": 233.9,
      "text": "And it is home to the native tribe that Finger Bone is from."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.26,
      "end": 236.64,
      "text": "They've lived in this area for thousands of years."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.74,
      "end": 237.0,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 237.14,
      "end": 244.58,
      "text": "And it has wetlands, desert, and it's also home to many, many species of birds, including pelicans."
    },
    {
      "start": 244.78,
      "end": 245.0,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 245.38,
      "end": 252.26,
      "text": "So nowadays it's a popular tourist spot if you like nature, camping, kayaking."
    },
    {
      "start": 252.5,
      "end": 254.14,
      "text": "There's a really big river."
    },
    {
      "start": 254.14,
      "end": 256.02,
      "text": "It's called the Murray River."
    },
    {
      "start": 256.24,
      "end": 261.32,
      "text": "The Murray River, the very end of this river, is where this film was made."
    },
    {
      "start": 261.42,
      "end": 261.78,
      "text": "Uh-huh."
    },
    {
      "start": 261.78,
      "end": 262.66,
      "text": "In the Kourang."
    },
    {
      "start": 262.96,
      "end": 263.26,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 263.68,
      "end": 270.64,
      "text": "So you can go kayaking down the river, end up in the Kourang, do some bird watching, barbecue, and camp."
    },
    {
      "start": 270.64,
      "end": 271.42,
      "text": "그래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.54,
      "end": 273.26,
      "text": "Barbecue가 빠질 수가 없는 거죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 273.44,
      "end": 274.08,
      "text": "Barbecue죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 274.48,
      "end": 275.42,
      "text": "특히 뮤직은 바비큐."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.04,
      "end": 276.46,
      "text": "그래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.86,
      "end": 286.2,
      "text": "이렇게 자연을 사랑하신다면 호주의 남북의 여행을 특히 이 섬 부분도 우리가 갈 수 있다는 정보를 알려주셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.2,
      "end": 290.64,
      "text": "근데 그 지역이 굉장히 평화로워 보였어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 290.64,
      "end": 295.88,
      "text": "근데 I've heard that it's threatened due to low water levels."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.88,
      "end": 297.06,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.16,
      "end": 300.2,
      "text": "Water's becoming lower and lower for some reason."
    },
    {
      "start": 300.76,
      "end": 304.76,
      "text": "So now it's under threat and especially the bird population."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.94,
      "end": 305.16,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 305.44,
      "end": 312.74,
      "text": "The low water levels is having a bad effect on the bird population because birds need water to find food."
    },
    {
      "start": 312.74,
      "end": 315.88,
      "text": "and that's part of important part of their habitat."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.3,
      "end": 318.88,
      "text": "So hopefully it needs to rain a lot."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.88,
      "end": 320.86,
      "text": "The water levels need to rise."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.98,
      "end": 321.32,
      "text": "그쵸."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.42,
      "end": 321.7,
      "text": "Somehow."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.12,
      "end": 322.24,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 323.04,
      "end": 326.84,
      "text": "자, 현재 그곳의 상황에 대해서도 한번 들어봤습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.46,
      "end": 329.38,
      "text": "자, 오늘 준비된 장면 듣고 올게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 330.14,
      "end": 331.24,
      "text": "We were having a picnic."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.98,
      "end": 334.85,
      "text": "Jenny and Belle, my little girl, are here."
    },
    {
      "start": 336.3,
      "end": 337.42,
      "text": "They went to get ice cream."
    },
    {
      "start": 338.47,
      "end": 339.59,
      "text": "I'm going to do anything special."
    },
    {
      "start": 340.66,
      "end": 341.72,
      "text": "Jenny wasn't speeding."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.72,
      "end": 346.96,
      "text": "Sometimes I think it's best not to have anyone to care about."
    },
    {
      "start": 348.18,
      "end": 349.08,
      "text": "Or you won't get hurt."
    },
    {
      "start": 350.64,
      "end": 353.32,
      "text": "I'd love to just go walk about like you fellas do."
    },
    {
      "start": 355.47,
      "end": 357.08,
      "text": "They can go pretty lonely."
    },
    {
      "start": 357.94,
      "end": 358.52,
      "text": "Sure enough, Tom."
    },
    {
      "start": 358.52,
      "end": 364.23,
      "text": "네, 이제 Fingerbone 아저씨랑 마이클의 아빠인 Tommy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.95,
      "end": 366.77,
      "text": "they are getting along well."
    },
    {
      "start": 366.97,
      "end": 369.17,
      "text": "Yeah, they're having a campfire together."
    },
    {
      "start": 369.57,
      "end": 370.79,
      "text": "Right by the beach."
    },
    {
      "start": 370.91,
      "end": 371.17,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 371.31,
      "end": 372.69,
      "text": "Oh, I love that scene."
    },
    {
      "start": 372.85,
      "end": 374.33,
      "text": "I love campfires."
    },
    {
      "start": 374.33,
      "end": 382.93,
      "text": "마음을 이제 활짝 열고 이제 Tom이 자신이 겪은 그 아픈 이야기를 나누는 장면이었습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 383.11,
      "end": 384.93,
      "text": "The conversation is not so pleasant."
    },
    {
      "start": 385.17,
      "end": 387.43,
      "text": "Very, very sad tragedy."
    },
    {
      "start": 387.63,
      "end": 387.91,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 388.01,
      "end": 390.59,
      "text": "He lost his wife and young daughter."
    },
    {
      "start": 390.75,
      "end": 391.11,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 391.47,
      "end": 394.25,
      "text": "So that's why they moved there in the first place."
    },
    {
      "start": 394.33,
      "end": 394.65,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 394.71,
      "end": 396.07,
      "text": "Because he was hurt by that."
    },
    {
      "start": 396.15,
      "end": 397.61,
      "text": "And he wanted to get away."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.13,
      "end": 398.69,
      "text": "떠나버리고."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.93,
      "end": 399.21,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 399.21,
      "end": 408.13,
      "text": "사실 아내와 딸이 had an accident, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 408.13,
      "end": 410.59,
      "text": "Yeah, they were in a car accident, a big car accident."
    },
    {
      "start": 410.59,
      "end": 416.71,
      "text": "And while they were having a picnic, just the wife and daughter went out for a minute to get something."
    },
    {
      "start": 416.85,
      "end": 418.15,
      "text": "To buy some ice cream."
    },
    {
      "start": 418.27,
      "end": 419.15,
      "text": "Buy some ice cream."
    },
    {
      "start": 419.25,
      "end": 419.41,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 419.41,
      "end": 424.47,
      "text": "And unfortunately, they had a tragic car accident and they lost their lives."
    },
    {
      "start": 424.47,
      "end": 434.03,
